ata. This novel framework enables improved empirical studies of peace. The book contributes nuanced understandings of peace in particular settings and demonstrates the multifaceted nature of peaceful relations - what is termed 'relational peace practices' - making important contributions to the field of studying peace beyond the absence of war.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aPeace-building. 0aPeace. 70(DE-588)4005248-50(DE-627)1063823650(DE-576)208859918aBegriff2gnd 70(DE-588)4071465-20(DE-627)1043598890(DE-576)209184051aFriede2gnd 70(DE-588)4073678-70(DE-627)1060918400(DE-576)209191147aKonfliktforschung2gnd 70(DE-588)4145198-30(DE-627)1055927220(DE-576)209739614aBeziehung2gnd 70(DE-588)4155435-80(DE-627)1055158840(DE-576)20981893XaFriedensforschung2gnd 70(DE-588)4204973-80(DE-627)1051392540(DE-576)210165766aKonzeption2gnd 70(DE-588)4679328-80(DE-627)3451703930(DE-576)214140407aFriedenssichernde Maßnahme2gnd 70(DE-588)7604836-60(DE-627)5602287400(DE-576)278419313aFriedenskonsolidierung2gnd 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Peace.2bisacsh1 aBramsen, Isabel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEklund, Niklas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElfving, Jörgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHedström, Jenny, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJarstad, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJarstad, Anna, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKlocek, Jason, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNilsson, Manuela, econtributor.4ctb4